Node.Notes: Uncertain. Many change lest to not. Tree assumes [her feet hold fast to Sheol] lest she observe the path of life.
Usually splendor/majesty. Some interpret as honor or strength (in the sense of manly vigor) in a few places like here.
"Little" in the sense of "nearly" in this pp use with K.:
""Assembly" and "congregation" seem to refer to the same referent, so that many translate as one term like "public assembly" since the point seems to be "in the sight of everyone.""

Node.Notes: Many take breasts as a symbol of love/affection/charm or as representing the whole body.
"Weigh out" or "make level." In v. 6, "ponder" (from "weigh out") usually favored. Sense of "scrutinize" likely here in light of first half of verse.
